solution.p:
We begin by isolating the trig ratio.
            8 \sin (\theta) - 1 \amp = 3 \amp \amp \blert{\text{Add 1 to both sides.}}
                 8 \sin (\theta) \amp = 4  \amp \amp \blert{\text{Divide both sides by 8.}}
                 \sin (\theta) \amp = \dfrac{4}{8} = \dfrac{1}{2}

